@ClareCraigPath Yes!

It's a fact we're being governed by FOOLS with a credential.

USEFOOLS! https://t.co/tvH5xTSb9D

@RobinAdamsOsteo Writing down what is right and wrong clearly isn't enough.

We have to accept that humans are flawed and mistakes will be made again in future.

Having pockets where things are done differently is the only way to show up such mistakes and as such decentralised power is critical.

@RobinAdamsOsteo I agree. It is important to focus on where we need to get to - but it might be a difficult long journey getting there.

It goes beyond just the failures of this particular fiasco.

Human rights' declarations were meant to stop some of the mistakes that were made and failed.
